  "local_port": 55042,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I open a Snapchat video that won't let me open?",
  "response": "If you're having trouble opening a Snapchat video, here are some steps you can try to resolve the issue:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Check Your Internet Connection**\n- Ensure you have a stable internet connection (Wi-Fi or mobile data).\n- If the connection is weak, the video may not load. Try switching networks or moving to a better location.\n\n---\n\n### **2. Restart the App**\n- Close Snapchat completely and relaunch it.\n- On iOS: Swipe up from the bottom of the screen (or double-click the Home button) and swipe Snapchat away.\n- On Android: Open the recent apps menu and swipe Snapchat away, or go to **Settings > Apps > Snapchat > Force Stop**.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Check for App Updates**\n- Make sure Snapchat is updated to the latest version.\n- Go to the **App Store** (iOS) or **Google Play Store** (Android) and check for updates.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Clear Cache (Android Only)**\n- Open **Settings > Apps > Snapchat > Storage**.\n- Tap **Clear Cache**. This will not delete your data but may resolve loading issues.\n\n---\n\n### **5. Restart Your Phone**\n- Sometimes, a simple restart can fix app-related issues.\n\n---\n\n### **6. Reinstall Snapchat**\n- Uninstall Snapchat and download it again from the App Store or Google Play Store.\n- Log in with your credentials and try opening the video again.\n\n---\n\n### **7. Check the Video\u2019s Status**\n- If the video is from another user, it\u2019s possible they deleted it or it expired.\n- If it\u2019s a cached or saved video, it may be corrupted and won\u2019t play.\n\n---\n\n### **8. Contact Snapchat Support**\n- If none of the above steps work, reach out to Snapchat Support:\n  - Open Snapchat > Profile > Settings (gear icon) > **Help > Support**.\n  - Explain the issue for further assistance.\n\n---\n\nLet me know if you need more help!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
